<L>__{exterior ocean close up: water morning light}
<A>__{we are at the delicate interface between ocean and air...liquid and gas...the event horizon where molecules evaporate. this interchange is ethereal. then, low frequencies rumble through depths...louder...closer, now... and the ocean surface is torn by a 46 foot catamaran and the roar of 2,700 horsepower, rocketing at us at 140 knots... offshore racer: "born to win" in profile. aerial: "born to win" ...has a canopy, low like a b 1 bomber and extends a half mile. it launches off two foot swells, goes airborne, pushes to 150 knots with another 1,100 rpm left...}
